Senate Resolution 414
By: Senators Kennedy of the 18th and Walker III of the 20th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Deputy Daryl Wayne Smallwood and dedicating a bridge
2 in his memory; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Deputy Daryl Wayne Smallwood served as a guardian of this nation's freedom
4 and liberty as a member of the United States Marine Corps, embodying the Marine values
5 of honor, courage, and commitment; and
6 WHEREAS, Deputy Smallwood was highly regarded by the citizens of his community and
7 state and by local government officials as a person of unquestioned integrity and dedication
8 to the sound principles of law enforcement; and
9 WHEREAS, he began his career in law enforcement with the Dooly County Sheriff's Office,
10 where he served with professionalism and honor for eight years, and he later served with the
11 Crisp County Sheriff's Office and the Peach County Sheriff's Office; and
12 WHEREAS, Deputy Smallwood's life was tragically cut short in November of 2016, when
13 he took on gunfire while responding to a neighbor dispute call; and
